---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Research Experiences | Portfolio" sideBarActiveItemID="experiences">
  <!-- Header Section -->
  <div class="mb-6">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold">Research Experiences</h1>
    <p class="text-base opacity-70 mt-2">
      An overview of my academic research and lab investigations.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- 1. Faint line after the description -->
  <hr class="border-base-300 my-8" />

  <!-- Experience Item 1: Wet Lab with Dr. Bhattacharya -->
  <div class="py-4">
    <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:justify-between sm:items-start gap-2 mb-4">
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary">Undergraduate Research Assistant</h2>
        <p class="text-md font-medium opacity-80">Dr. Subhrajit Bhattacharya's Lab | Keck Graduate Institute</p>
      </div>
      <span class="badge badge-outline py-3 px-4 text-sm font-semibold">June 2026 - July 2026</span>
    </div>
    
    <!-- Research Project/Experience Details -->
    <div class="space-y-4 text-base text-justify leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        Currently conducting wet lab research under the mentorship of Dr. Bhattacharya. My project investigates the effect of alcohol on Alzheimer's Disease-Related Dementia, specifically how ethanol exposure induces downregulation in proteins such as GluN2B, Alpha-7, and PSD-95. 
      </p>
      <p>
        To achieve this, I utilize key laboratory techniques such as Western Blots and gel electrophoresis. I played a role in troubleshooting the lab's Western Blot protocol for progress reports, such as by adjusting different chemical reagents used and the amount of protein loaded over the course of many trials-and-errors. 
      </p>
      <p>
        This experience has strengthened my experience in hands-on proficiency with protein extraction, quantification, and analysis within a wet-lab environment. 
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
  
  <!-- 2. Faint line after the experience entry -->
  <hr class="border-base-300 my-8" />
</BaseLayout>
  
</BaseLayout>
